   "source": [
    "# ðŸ§¬ Genomics Workshop â€” Google Colab\n",
    "\n",
    "Welcome! This notebook contains the **full workshop pipeline** that installs required tools, clones the workshop repository, downloads example data, runs QC, trimming, mapping, variant calling, filtering, and a simple PCA.\n",
    "\n",
    "**NOTE:** Installation may take 5â€“15 minutes."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Verify Python version and working directory\n",
    "import sys, os\n",
    "print('Python:', sys.version)\n",
    "!pwd\n",
    "!ls -la\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 1) Clone the workshop repository"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Clone the GitHub repository\n",
    "!if [ -d Genomics_learning_workshop ]; then echo 'Repo already exists'; else git clone https://github.com/PoODL-CES/Genomics_learning_workshop.git; fi\n",
    "!ls -la Genomics_learning_workshop | head -n 120\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 2) Install bioinformatics tools"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Update package lists\n",
    "!sudo apt-get update -qq\n",
    "!sudo apt-get install -y -qq bwa samtools bcftools fastqc unzip plink python3-pip default-jre\n",
    "!pip install --quiet pandas matplotlib seaborn cutadapt\n",
    "# Trim Galore script\n",
    "!wget -q https://raw.githubusercontent.com/FelixKrueger/TrimGalore/master/trim_galore\n",
    "!chmod +x trim_galore\n",
    "!./trim_galore --version || true\n",
    "# Report versions\n",
    "!bwa 2>&1 | head -n 1\n",
    "!samtools --version | head -n 1\n",
    "!bcftools --version | head -n 1\n",
    "!fastqc --version\n",
    "!plink --version\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 3) Install GATK"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "!if [ -f gatk.zip ]; then echo 'GATK already downloaded'; else wget -q -O gatk.zip https://github.com/broadinstitute/gatk/releases/download/4.2.6.1/gatk-4.2.6.1.zip; fi\n",
    "!unzip -q -o gatk.zip -d /content/gatk\n",
    "!java -jar /content/gatk/gatk-package-4.2.6.1-local.jar --help | head -n 5\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 4) Download example dataset"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "!mkdir -p dataset\n",
    "%cd dataset\n",
    "!if [ -f ngs_dataset.zip ]; then echo 'dataset already present'; else wget -q https://zenodo.org/records/14258052/files/ngs_dataset.zip || echo 'please download manually'; fi\n",
    "!if [ -f ngs_dataset.zip ]; then unzip -q -o ngs_dataset.zip; fi\n",
    "!ls -la | head -n 200\n",
    "%cd ..\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 5) FastQC"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "!mkdir -p fastqc_reports\n",
    "!fastqc -t 2 dataset/*.fastq.gz -o fastqc_reports || echo 'FastQC skipped'\n",
    "!ls -la fastqc_reports || true\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 6) Trim Galore"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "R1=$(ls dataset/*_R1*.fastq.gz 2>/dev/null | head -n1)\n",
    "R2=$(ls dataset/*_R2*.fastq.gz 2>/dev/null | head -n1)\n",
    "echo 'R1='${R1}\n",
    "echo 'R2='${R2}\n",
    "if [ -n \"$R1\" -a -n \"$R2\" ]; then mkdir -p trimmed_reads; ./trim_galore --paired $R1 $R2 -o trimmed_reads || echo 'TrimGalore failed'; else echo 'Paired FASTQ not found'; fi\n",
    "!ls -la trimmed_reads || true\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 7) Mapping with BWA, sort, index"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "REF=$(ls Genomics_learning_workshop/reference/*.fasta 2>/dev/null | head -n1 || true)\n",
    "if [ -z \"$REF\" ]; then REF=$(ls dataset/*.fasta 2>/dev/null | head -n1 || true); fi\n",
    "echo 'Reference:' $REF\n",
    "if [ -n \"$REF\" ]; then \n",
    "  bwa index $REF || echo 'bwa index failed'; \
",
    "  R1=$(ls trimmed_reads/*_val_1*.fq.gz 2>/dev/null | head -n1 || true); R2=$(ls trimmed_reads/*_val_2*.fq.gz 2>/dev/null | head -n1 || true); \
",
    "  if [ -n \"$R1\" -a -n \"$R2\" ]; then bwa mem -t 2 $REF $R1 $R2 > aln.sam || echo 'bwa mem failed'; else echo 'No reads to map'; fi; \
",
    "  if [ -f aln.sam ]; then samtools view -bS aln.sam > aln.bam || true; samtools sort aln.bam -o aln.sorted.bam || true; samtools index aln.sorted.bam || true; fi\n",
    "else echo 'Reference not found'; fi\n",
    "!ls -la *.bam *.sam || true\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 8) Variant calling with bcftools"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "if [ -f aln.sorted.bam -a -n \"$REF\" ]; then \n",
    "  bcftools mpileup -f $REF aln.sorted.bam -Ou | bcftools call -mv -Oz -o raw_variants.vcf.gz || echo 'bcftools call failed'; \n",
    "  bcftools index raw_variants.vcf.gz || true; \n",
    "else echo 'BAM or reference missing'; fi\n",
    "!ls -la raw_variants.vcf.gz* || true\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 9) Filter variants"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "if [ -f raw_variants.vcf.gz ]; then \n",
    "  bcftools filter -i 'DP>5 & QUAL>30' raw_variants.vcf.gz -Ov -o filtered_variants.vcf || echo 'Filtering failed'; \n",
    "  ls -lh filtered_variants.vcf || true; \n",
    "else echo 'No VCF to filter'; fi\n"
   ]
  }
